temp.fibHeap.stixar.graph
Interface Edge

All Superinterfaces:
Attributable
All Known Implementing Classes:
BasicEdge, BasicUEdge
public interface Edge
extends Attributable

Simple linked-list like interface for edges (readonly). This interface defines a minimal edge interface. Programmers may implement this and the corresponding Node interfaces with a minimum of effort and then benefit from all the supplied read-only graph algorithms.

Method Detail

source

Node source()
Return the node from which this edge emanates. Directed/Undirected Caveats:
  • If this edge is a directed edge, this method will always return the same value.
  • If this edge is an undirected edge, and is accessed through a (possibly empty) sequence of calls to next() following a call to Node.out() for a node u, then this method will return u.

target

Node target()
Return the node to which this edge points. Directed/Undirected Caveats:
  • If this edge is a directed edge, this method will always return the same value.
  • If this edge is an undirected edge, and is accessed through a (possibly empty) sequence of calls to next() following a call to Node.out() for a node u, then this method will return the vertex opposing u.

next

Edge next()
Return the next edge in the linked list of edges, or null if no such edge exists.

Directed/Undirected Caveats:

The linked list whose existence is implied by this method should respect the conventions detailed in the Node.out() method.

Returns:
the next edge in a list defined by the Node.out() method.

edgeId

int edgeId()
Give a unique edge identifier.

Directed/Undirected Caveats:

An edge must be equal to another edge iff their edgeIds are equal. This mechanism can be used to make pairs of objects assume the identity of a single edge which can be useful in making undirected edges.
